Sounds of the Singing School. (Round in Five Parts.)
P. P. BLISS.
42
Divide the class into five divisions and number them, (make two divisions of Soprano or any part that is most numerous) First division sings first staff alone. When
first division begins second staff, second division begins piece. When second division begins second staff, and first division third staff, third division begins piece, and
so on. Sing the piece through twice, the divisions ending one after another as they begin, or together at the end of any staff all singing the word "away." The teacher
may make a vocal training exercise of this by calling out while they are singing,-"piano, forte, cres., dim., legato, staccato, forzando, clear, somber," &c.
